<node id="Canvas">
  <data key="d0">Canvas</data>
  <data key="d1">platform</data>
  <data key="d2">Canvas is an online platform that serves as a central hub for various academic activities and resources within an educational context. It functions as a comprehensive repository for course materials, including supplementary reading materials, required textbooks (such as for CSCE 669), and notes for specific academic works like "Introduction to Tractability and Approximability of Optimization Problems." The platform is designated for assignment management, facilitating the posting and submission of homework assignments and machine problems, and is the required online system for all assignment submissions. Canvas also lists important dates, encompassing assignment due dates (including those for specific courses like the Machine Learning Course) and exam dates, with a general guideline that all assignments are due by 11:59 pm unless otherwise specified. Furthermore, the platform provides a means for students to contact their instructors. While Canvas can display total scores for assignments, users should be aware that these figures may occasionally be slightly inaccurate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e71d1b10edbe0c32853ef56c45777750&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c58ee951c223e7f4cf49991a748f302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a863d6fab8e70ebbab93357f389a2a60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5f93f882082dd2e8bd9f6fea3705879&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cbc6507438dd741ecc6e529fe954278&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce19d80ec4482577c0c7dfdb40a6b6a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01bc4d956199eea04809225050dec80b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2384cead57358b5db5cb910f416830cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-007361532f5a9b6614541c85881c7ed9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774773367</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Grading Policy">
  <data key="d0">Grading Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">A Grading Policy defines the comprehensive structure for evaluating student performance within a course, detailing how final course grades are determined. It specifies the various components that contribute to the overall grade, their respective weights or point values, and the specific scale used to convert numerical scores into letter grades.

This policy outlines the distribution of grades across common components such as homework assignments, projects, exams, quizzes, exercises, and participation. The weighting of these components can vary significantly; for example, one policy might assign Homework 30%, Course project 35%, and a Final exam 35%, while another could allocate Assignments 31%, Quizzes 40%, Course Project 26%, and Participation 3%. Some policies may set a total possible score, such as 1000 points for the course, noting that the total scores for daily quizzes and homework assignments might vary slightly from a fixed point value by the end of a semester.

A critical element of a Grading Policy is the definition of the letter grading scale. A widely adopted standard scale typically defines an A as 90-100%, B as 80-89%, C as 70-79%, D as 60-69%, and F for anything below 60%. However, specific policies may express these cutoffs differently or utilize alternative scales; for example, one definition specifies cutoffs such as "A at most 90%, B at most 80%, C at most 70%, D at most 60%, and F for anything below 60%," indicating a distinct approach to grade boundaries. Additionally, some policies explicitly mention the possibility of applying a curve to adjust final grades.&lt;SEP&gt;This policy outlines the percentage contribution of each graded component to the final grade and details the 10-point letter grade scale.&lt;SEP&gt;The grading policy outlines the weight distribution of different grade components for the course, including weekly assessments, homework, and an individual semester-long project, along with the letter grade thresholds.&lt;SEP&gt;The policy outlining how students' performance will be evaluated and graded in the course.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e71d1b10edbe0c32853ef56c45777750&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1eabe31ef1e00dc32e0dbd929dab069a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c53b1e368af6bad831cd9b96486285d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfa1933458123176fbbd95a49ddd5dac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942343fa7db4b93679179e294760f458&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-381218105af92b28f283452a63c63ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24d121840ef425d19d7f4be65a994242&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-007361532f5a9b6614541c85881c7ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-073f3905d25e07b3de0c6af600fbb64b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226a3d7b35279fb5024bf203866c977e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4084eda47ece732e28955a2801108cb1</data>
