<node id="Final Exam">
  <data key="d0">Final Exam</data>
  <data key="d1">exam</data>
  <data key="d2">The Final Exam is an examination component typically administered as the concluding assessment for a course. It is often characterized as a comprehensive exam, designed to evaluate a student's overall understanding of the course material. These examinations are commonly conducted in-class.

The contribution of a Final Exam to a course's overall grading scheme can vary significantly. Some instances indicate that it contributes a specific percentage, such as 30% or 35%, to the final grade. In other contexts, its value may be expressed in points, for example, contributing to a total of 400 points when combined with a Midterm examination. Notably, there are also instances where an examination component, referred to as a Final Exam, is explicitly not included in the course's grading scheme.

Specific Final Exams have been scheduled at various times and dates. Examples include an exam scheduled for Monday, May 4, from 10:30 AM to 12:30 PM. Other occurrences might be scheduled for Thursday, April 30th, from 3:00 PM to 4:00 PM, typically in the classroom, or for Friday, May 1, from 8:00 AM to 10:00 AM.&lt;SEP&gt;A comprehensive final exam accounting for 30% of the total grade, scheduled for May 4 from 3:30 PM to 5:30 PM in HRBB 113.&lt;SEP&gt;The Final Exam is a comprehensive exam comprising 30% of the final grade, scheduled from 3:30 - 5:30 PM on May 4 in HRBB 113.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e71d1b10edbe0c32853ef56c45777750&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa3afc12a670cd1cb0dbbd58a21ee6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1eabe31ef1e00dc32e0dbd929dab069a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d770ff61e6e4e9869576a11fffdbad2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a863d6fab8e70ebbab93357f389a2a60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d188bffad2de46a2d40cc892e31ab869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e6d8f1fb0868aaa777c3b4e865fd4d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-007361532f5a9b6614541c85881c7ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4375e28268d2a8a30d4105aa2942d3a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdd535fdf10cab1c91d762a5888f4e9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774773457</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Grading Scale">
  <data key="d0">Grading Scale</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">This policy defines the percentage ranges for letter grades: A = 90-100%, B = 70-89%, C = 60-69%, F = 0-59%.&lt;SEP&gt;A set of criteria defining letter grades (A, B, C, D, F) based on numerical score ranges.&lt;SEP&gt;A component defining the grade ranges for letter grades A, B, C, D, and F.&lt;SEP&gt;Defines the percentage ranges for letter grades: A (90-100%), B (70-89%), C (60-70%), F (0-59%).&lt;SEP&gt;The policy that defines the letter grades (A, B, C, D, F) corresponding to numerical score ranges.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e71d1b10edbe0c32853ef56c45777750&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49cbdcaf6f02cb17eb1de01b94ff2d2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01bc4d956199eea04809225050dec80b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-007361532f5a9b6614541c85881c7ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4084eda47ece732e28955a2801108cb1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774773689</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Late Work Policy">
  <data key="d0">Late Work Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">The Late Work Policy is a general guideline or policy that governs the submission of assignments after their designated deadline, establishing rules and outlining penalties for such late submissions. A consistent and frequently referenced provision within this policy dictates that makeup work required due to an excused absence is specifically exempt from its provisions and is not categorized as late work, nor is it subject to late work penalties. This exemption often references "Student Rule 7."

In specific applications of the Late Work Policy, stricter submission requirements may be enforced. For instance, some iterations may require all assignments to be submitted exclusively via a designated platform, such as Canvas, and explicitly state that no late submissions or submissions via email will be accepted. Under such circumstances, only work submitted on time is considered for evaluation, including eligibility for partial credit.&lt;SEP&gt;A general policy defining rules for work submitted after deadlines, with an exception for excused absences.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e71d1b10edbe0c32853ef56c45777750&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-491622aa2feb07cb2cecb5393f78ed43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d11c13929103dfefb983be96841e8dd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c53b1e368af6bad831cd9b96486285d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfa1933458123176fbbd95a49ddd5dac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a863d6fab8e70ebbab93357f389a2a60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49cbdcaf6f02cb17eb1de01b94ff2d2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-381218105af92b28f283452a63c63ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01bc4d956199eea04809225050dec80b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24d121840ef425d19d7f4be65a994242&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d188bffad2de46a2d40cc892e31ab869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-007361532f5a9b6614541c85881c7ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdd535fdf10cab1c91d762a5888f4e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-073f3905d25e07b3de0c6af600fbb64b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-963f08e9468a8386b210c963f7d81dd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4084eda47ece732e28955a2801108cb1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774773689</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Student Rule 7">
  <data key="d0">Student Rule 7</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">Student Rule 7 is a foundational university, student, and academic rule that primarily establishes comprehensive guidelines concerning excused absences. It provides detailed information, including specific definitions of what constitutes an excused absence, the necessary documentation requirements, and applicable timelines. Additionally, this rule outlines the procedures and guidelines for makeup work necessitated by such excused absences.

This rule is widely referenced by various academic policies, including general Late Work Policies and specific course-level policies, such as the Machine Learning Course Late Work Policy. In doing so, Student Rule 7 informs the procedures for handling late submissions and stipulates that makeup work due to excused absences is typically exempt from standard late work policies.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific university or academic rule referenced in connection with the Late Work Policy.&lt;SEP&gt;A rule referenced by the General Late Work Policy concerning makeup work for excused absences.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific rule referenced as the basis for exempting makeup work for excused absences from the late work policy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e71d1b10edbe0c32853ef56c45777750&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-491622aa2feb07cb2cecb5393f78ed43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4645a5b8880a1c596bee106a995c6ffd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d11c13929103dfefb983be96841e8dd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c53b1e368af6bad831cd9b96486285d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfa1933458123176fbbd95a49ddd5dac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49cbdcaf6f02cb17eb1de01b94ff2d2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce19d80ec4482577c0c7dfdb40a6b6a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-381218105af92b28f283452a63c63ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01bc4d956199eea04809225050dec80b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24d121840ef425d19d7f4be65a994242&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d188bffad2de46a2d40cc892e31ab869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-007361532f5a9b6614541c85881c7ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdd535fdf10cab1c91d762a5888f4e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-073f3905d25e07b3de0c6af600fbb64b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-963f08e9468a8386b210c963f7d81dd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f069ee0621606806c1d09b87e5cc4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4084eda47ece732e28955a2801108cb1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774773689</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Course Specific Late Work Policy">
  <data key="d0">Course Specific Late Work Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">A Course Specific Late Work Policy establishes the guidelines and consequences for submitting academic work past its official due date within a particular course, potentially overriding or complementing a general institutional policy. This policy encompasses various types of assignments, including homework, project assignments, online quizzes, machine problems, project proposals, and reports.

Policies can vary significantly depending on the assignment type. Some policies explicitly state that no late submissions will be accepted, applying to assignments such as homework, project assignments, Assignment 0, and Project Presentations. In these instances, email submissions are typically disregarded, though students may be advised to discuss unusual circumstances with the instructor in advance.

Conversely, other aspects of the policy detail penalties for late submissions. A frequent penalty structure involves a deduction of 20% of the full grade per day late. Specific requirements may include submissions being due by 10 am, with no points awarded after five days of delay, and delays being rounded up to the nearest day. Some policies grant a limited number of "late days" for the entire course, such as five, which may not be applicable to all assignments, like the final project. Additionally, the policy may stipulate that only on-time work is eligible for partial credit.&lt;SEP&gt;A detailed policy for the course stating that all late submissions lose 20% points per delayed day and are not accepted five days after the deadline without instructor permission.&lt;SEP&gt;A policy stating that assignments and the project are due on designated dates at the beginning of class, and no late submissions will be accepted unless discussed with the instructor in advance.&lt;SEP&gt;A policy detailing the late day system specifically for homework submissions in the course.&lt;SEP&gt;This policy details specific late submission rules for write-ups and other assignments, including deduction percentages and maximum late periods.&lt;SEP&gt;A policy specifying a 1% per hour penalty for late homework assignments, up to a maximum of 48 hours, after which the assignment receives a 0.&lt;SEP&gt;The specific late submission rules for this course, including penalties and acceptance period.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e71d1b10edbe0c32853ef56c45777750&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-491622aa2feb07cb2cecb5393f78ed43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d11c13929103dfefb983be96841e8dd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c53b1e368af6bad831cd9b96486285d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfa1933458123176fbbd95a49ddd5dac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49cbdcaf6f02cb17eb1de01b94ff2d2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-381218105af92b28f283452a63c63ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01bc4d956199eea04809225050dec80b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d188bffad2de46a2d40cc892e31ab869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-007361532f5a9b6614541c85881c7ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdd535fdf10cab1c91d762a5888f4e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-073f3905d25e07b3de0c6af600fbb64b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f069ee0621606806c1d09b87e5cc4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4084eda47ece732e28955a2801108cb1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774773689</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Course Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Course Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">scheduleevent</data>
  <data key="d2">A Course Schedule is a comprehensive plan or timeline that details the structure and progression of a course. It typically outlines the weekly topics, the sequence of lectures, and includes important due dates for assignments and other significant course events. While it may specify a duration, such as a 15-week period, a Course Schedule is often presented as a tentative or rough outline and is subject to change.&lt;SEP&gt;This schedule provides a weekly breakdown of topics and activities for the course over 15 weeks.&lt;SEP&gt;A section outlining the weekly topics and due dates for the course.&lt;SEP&gt;A detailed plan outlining weekly course topics, associated dates, and assignment due dates.</data>
