<node id="Operating Systems Course">
  <data key="d0">Operating Systems Course</data>
  <data key="d1">course</data>
  <data key="d2">A course focusing on operating systems, requiring students to leverage knowledge from Computer Architecture and Computer Systems to understand and implement various aspects such as memory management, persistent storage, file systems, threading, scheduling, resource management, virtualization, and distributed systems. A key component is the implementation of a simple operating system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4e07d2270f14ba28891fb49568e5ffd1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774772715</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
