<node id="Python">
  <data key="d0">Python</data>
  <data key="d1">programminglanguage</data>
  <data key="d2">Python is a permitted programming language for assignments, and programs written in it must be executable on CS unix hosts or public systems in the department lab.&lt;SEP&gt;Python is the programming language required for all programming assignments.&lt;SEP&gt;A programming language that students are expected to learn rapidly for the course, without prior exposure being a prerequisite.&lt;SEP&gt;Students are expected to rapidly come up to speed with Python for homework assignments, even if they have no prior exposure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2cbc6507438dd741ecc6e529fe954278&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4375e28268d2a8a30d4105aa2942d3a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226a3d7b35279fb5024bf203866c977e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-963f08e9468a8386b210c963f7d81dd4</data>
